NATION; 
JIM BAKKER MOVED TO MINNESOTA 
Convicted swindler Jim Bakker today received his expected transfer from a 
federal prison in Alabama to one in Minnesota to serve his time for defrauding 
followers of his PTL television ministry, officials said. 
He arrived at the prison system's Federal Medical Center here at about 11:45 
a.m. after being transferred from the Federal Correctional Institution at 
Talladega, Ala. 
Bakker, 49, was sentenced Oct. 24 by a federal judge in Charlotte, N.C., to 45 
years in prison and fined $500,000. 
